
By REUTERSAPRIL 23, 2018, 4:49 A.M. E.D.T.

SEOUL —  The South Korean government said on Monday it would join forces to help normalize General Motors Co's South Korean unit.
The government said in a statement that it respected a tentative wage deal struck between the company and the union.
(Reporting by Ju-min Park; Editing by Muralikumar Anantharaman)
